{"header":{"word":"יַּעֲקב","entry":7351,"letter":"ע","strongs":3290,"page":784},"definitions":[{"title":"Def","body":" [[יַּעֲקב]]:344, [[יַעֲקוֹב]]:5 ","content":"definition","show":"block"},{"title":"n.pr.m.","body":" et ","content":"definition","show":"block"},{"title":"gent","body":". Jacob, <span class=\"greek\">Iakwb</span>, son of Isaac and Rebekah, father of tribes of Isr. (expl. fr. [[עָקֵב]] heel Ge 25:26, Ho 12:4; i.e. supplanter; cp. with [[עָקַב]] overreach Ge 27:36; one closely following acc. to Lag:BN 127; connexion with Pal. city (?) called in Egyptian Y&#8216;kb&#8217;ara (i.e. [[יַעֲקׂב־אֵל]]) is obscure; cf. Mey:ZAW vi.1 ff. WMM:As. u. Eur. 162 ff. Jen:ZA x(1895&#8211;6), 347 ff.; v.also Bab. n.pr.m. Ya&#239;&#7731;ubilu, Pinches in Hom:AHT 61, 96, 112; hence OT [[יַעֲקׂב]] perhaps orig. [[יעקבקל]] or the like. cf. Palm. n.pr. [[בלעקב]], [[עתעקב]]);&#8212;[[יַעֲקוֹב]] Je 30:18 + 3 t. Je, Le 26:42; [[יַעֲקׂב]] 215 t. Hex. (chiefly JE; 180 t. Gn once Lv, etc.), 34 t. Ps 42 t. Is (27 t. 40&#8211;66), etc.;&#8212;","content":"definition","show":"block"},{"title":"1.","body":" as ","content":"definition","show":"block"},{"title":"n.pr.m.","body":" Ge 25:26 + 205 t. (+ [[אַבְרָהָם]], [[יִחְחָק]]19 t.); also &#180;[[בֵּית יַע]] of people (v. [[בַּיִת]] ","content":"definition","show":"block"},{"title":"5 d","body":" (<span class=\"greek\">g</span>)), &#180;[[בְּנֵי יַע]] (v. [[בֵּן]] ","content":"definition","show":"block"},{"title":"1 j","body":" (<span class=\"greek\">b</span>)), &#180;[[זֶרַע יַע]] (v. [[זֶרַע]] ","content":"definition","show":"block"},{"title":"4 f","body":"), &#180;[[עֵין יַע]] (v. [[עַיִן]] ), etc. ","content":"definition","show":"block"},{"title":"2.","body":" as ","content":"definition","show":"block"},{"title":"n.pr.gent.","body":" (c. 100 t.; poet. and proph.) Nu 24:5, Nu 24:19, De 32:9, Ps 44:5, Is 10:21, Is 17:4, Je 10:25, Je 30:7 +; &#8214;[[יִשְׂרָאֵל]] Nu 23:7, De 33:10, Is 14:1, Ps 14:7 + c. 35 t.; specif. of N. Isr. Am 7:2, Am 7:5, Ho 12:13 (+ Ho 10:11, Ho 12:3 prob., v. Now), Mic 1:5, Mic 1:5, Is 9:7; of Judah Mic 3:1, Mic 3:8, Ob:Ob 10, Is 65:9, Mal 2:12 + al. post-exilic; &#180;[[גְּאוֹן יַע]] v. [[גׇּאוֹן]]; &#134; &#180;[[אֵל יַע]] Ps 146:5, &#180;[[אֱלוֹהַּ יַע]] Ps 114:7 &#134;; &#180;[[אֱלֽהֵי יַע]] 2Sa 23:1, Is 2:3 = Mic 4:2 + 9 t. PsalmPsalm + Ps 24:6 (&#180;[[יַע]] &#180;[[א]] for MT &#180;[[יַע]] alone), so LXX SyrVer Vulgate Ew Ol Hup Bae We Che al.; read &#180;[[יַע]] &#180;[[א]] also prob. 2Sa 23:2 (for &#180;[[יִשׂ]] &#180;[[א]], &#8214;&#180;[[חוּר יִשׂ]]) Vulgate HPS; &#180;[[קְדוֹשׁ יַע]] Is 29:23 (&#8214;&#180;[[יִשׂ]] &#180;[[א]]); &#180;[[מֶלֶךְ יַע]] Is 41:21 (&#8214;[[יהוה]]).&#8212; On [[יַעֲקׂב]] v. esp. Dr: &#8216;Jacob&#8217; in Hastings:Dict. Bib. ii. 526 ff.\r","content":"definition","show":"block"}],"notes":"","etymology":[],"morphology":[]}